Dear Freshers,

On behalf of the Chemical Engineering Association of NIT Raipur (CHEANIT) ,we are thrilled to invite you to the official college welcome party for freshers!

This party is a celebration of your new beginning as college students. It is a chance to meet your new classmates, professors, and other members of the college community. It is also a chance to let loose and have some fun before the start of the academic year.

The party will be held on 29/09/23 (Time - 2pm to 6 pm)

So, those who are interested to perform in any of the following categories can give the names to your CR by Tomorrow -
1.Song(group/solo)
2.Dance(group/solo)
3.Skit(group)
4.Poetry
5.Rap


**Dress Code - **
Boys - Formals(shirt - pant and tie will be compulsory)
Girls - Traditional wear


**Sincerely,**
 Aparna Gupta
President

29/09/2023, 15:39 - Khushi Hansrajani Cr Chem.: *NCC Recruitment Drive*

a) Students shortlisted for the physical round are hereby instructed to reach NIT Campus as per the below details:-

*Date:* 30/09/2023 (Tomorrow)
*Venue:* In front of Academic building (Near Central Garden)
*Time:*  6:30 am sharp

*Note*: Late comers will be not be allowed for further process, so be on time.

b) *Dress code*: Sports wear/Track suit and sports shoes.

c) Bring your own notebook, pen and water bottles.

Students are instructed to have a light breakfast as the process will be time taking and no break will be provided in between.

d) Those who have NCC A and B Certificates or SSB call letters are instructed to bring them. (Online copies will also be accepted)
- Those who got conference out should show the photo taken in SSB board.

- From
5CG CT(I) COY NCC, NIT Raipur

20/12/2023, 13:03 - VISHIKA NANDWANA: Dear NIT Raipur students,
 
We're happy to open applications for the *Finlatics Stock Market Analyst program*, an online *live project* that helps students gain *practical exposure* to the *Equity Markets* at the *National Institute Of Technology, Raipur*. 

*No prior domain knowledge* is required to be a part of the project.

The project runs at leading institutes including *IIT Bombay*, *IIT Madras*, *NIT Delhi* and *BITS Pilani* among others.

Benefits post-completion: 
1. *Certificate of Work  Experience*
2. *Letter of Recommendation*.

To apply, please use the link below: 

https://www.finlatics.com/fm-FnO/application/index.php?utm_src=nitraiw

*Project Duration* : 2 months

*Project start*: Flexible on student choice. To balance it along with exams or assignments, students can choose to start once they are completed. 

*Project Break*: Students can also take a break on the project in case they need it for exams or assignments. 

*Time Commitment*: 4-5 hours per week

If selected, the program has a minimal induction fee: of Rs. 1499 + GST (on student choice).

*Fee Waiver*: A fee waiver of *30%* shall be given to all *National Institute Of Technology, Raipur* students on the abovementioned minimal induction fee. This will *reduce the fee* to Rs. 999 + GST.

*No payment* has to be made right now 

The *application* process would take *2-3 mins* of your time. 

Best regards,
Team Finlatics

*Rules and Regulations:*

This event consists of 2 rounds.

Prelim: *Talent round*
In this round, the participants have to showcase the talents that they possess. Talent can include singing, dancing, poetry recital, stand-up comedy, immense fashion sense or any other.
The duration of the performance can be up to 2 minutes maximum.

The judging criteria will be :
a. Quality of performance.
b. Uniqueness of the performed talent.
c. Utilisation of the given time.
Ten participants each from boys and girls will be selected for the final round.

Final round: *Ramp walk & Q/A round*.
a. In this round, the shortlisted contestants will be asked
questions based on a number of topics such as current
affairs, history, culture, etc.
b. The dress code for this round will be ethnic ( Saree for girls
& Kurta for boys).

The judgment will be done on the following criteria:
1) The overall presentation of the participant ( Dress-up,
confidence and the overall behavior).
2) The quality of the answer given by the participant.
3) Confidence level.

13/02/2024, 12:20 - Abhinesh Tyagi Chemical '26: Painting Competition at Sustainable Souvenir Walkway under the aegis of Viksit Bharat@2047

Organized by: Go-Green Eco-social Committee, NIT Raipur

Cash prizes for the winners will be as follows:

1st Prize: Rs. 21001/-

2nd Prize: Rs.16001/-

3rd Prize: Rs: 11001/-

Complimentary Prizes for remaining shortlisted teams: 1001/-

Environmental sustainability refers to the responsible use and preservation of natural resources to meet the needs of the present without compromising the ability of future generations to meet their own needs.

In this regard as per the vision of Honorable Director NIT Raipur, the Go Green-Eco Social Committee of NIT Raipur proposed to conduct a Painting Competition to spread awareness through beautiful wall painting in Souvenir Garden Walkway.

The theme of the painting competition encompasses various principles and practices aimed at maintaining ecological balance, protecting biodiversity, and ensuring the longevity of ecosystems.

All the interested students (individual/group) are required to submit the design sample copy (Handmade/Computer Made) to the office of the Dean (SW) by 15/02/2023 to participate in the Painting Competition. The institute administration will short list and finalize 25 designs (approximately) for the painting on the boundary wall panels at Sustainable Souvenir Walkway. All the shortlisted team/students will be required to paint the submitted design on the wall panels of Sustainable Souvenir Walkway, NIT Raipur.

Painting may be 2D or 3D.

All the raw material for final paintings will be provided by Go-Green Club, NIT Raipur.

All the students of Architecture and other disciplines are requested to participate in this painting competition.

Here are few themes of environmental sustainability for the painting competition:

Conservation of Resources:

Sustainable practices focus on using resources efficiently and avoiding unnecessary waste. This includes responsible consumption of water, energy, electricity, raw materials, and other natural resources.

Renewable Energy:

Transitioning from non-renewable energy sources (such as fossil fuels) to renewable energy (solar, wind, hydro, geothermal) is a critical aspect of environmental sustainability. This reduces dependence on finite resources and minimizes environmental impact.

 

Biodiversity Conservation:

Protecting and preserving biodiversity is essential for environmental sustainability. This involves maintaining natural habitats, preventing habitat destruction, and implementing conservation measures for endangered species.

Waste Reduction, Recycling and Reuse:

Sustainable practices emphasize reducing waste generation and promoting recycling. This helps in minimizing the environmental impact of landfills, conserving resources, and reducing pollution.

Sustainable Agriculture:

Agriculture plays a crucial role in environmental sustainability. Sustainable farming practices prioritize soil health, water conservation, and biodiversity preservation. This includes organic farming, crop rotation, and agroecological approaches.

Green Infrastructure:

Developing green infrastructure, such as green roofs, urban parks, and sustainable urban planning, contributes to environmental sustainability in urban areas. These initiatives enhance biodiversity, reduce the urban heat island effect, and improve overall quality of life.

Climate Change Mitigation:

Environmental sustainability involves efforts to mitigate climate change by reducing greenhouse gas emissions. This includes adopting cleaner technologies, promoting carbon sequestration, and supporting international agreements focused on climate action.

Empowered Indian:

Leaders from the political, scientific, cultural and other arenas for achievable and essential national goals. Encompassing education, health, sports, Nari Shakti, caring society, and culture.

Sustainable Economy:

Practices that support long-term economic growth without negatively impacting social, environmental, and cultural aspects of the community. The greatest amount of general well-being with the least amount of resource use and environmental harm. Spanning agriculture, industry, services, infrastructure, energy, and the green economy.

Innovation, Science and Technology:

Science and innovation hold solutions to many shared challenges, ranging from managing water to delivering infrastructure, health, and education services over distances. Global research and development hub for sophisticated sectors like network equipment, medical equipment, aerospace, automotive, biotechnology and computation. Current trends point to the advent of a suite of new digital technologies, such as machine learning, optimization, artificial intelligence, robotics, and startup initiatives.

Good Governance:

The processes and institutions produce results that meet the needs of society while making the best use of resources at their disposal. It demonstrates accountability, leadership, integrity, stewardship, and transparency. Addressing the pillars of effective governance and national security.

Air Pollution: Health &Well-Being

Clean air keeps you healthy and you can enjoy your life with your healthy body. Clean air is considered as one of the basic requirements for human beings. Pollution-related diseases due to air pollution continue to rise at an alarming rate and affect peopleâ€™s quality of life. Air pollution also adversely affects welfare inequality. Air pollution as a significant risk factor affects health and sense of subjective well-being.

Swachh Bharat Abhiyan:

Swachh Bharat Abhiyan, is a country-wide campaign initiated by the Government of India  to eliminate open defecation and improve solid waste management and to create Open Defecation Free (ODF) villages.

International Year of Millets:

Millets have been an integral part of our diet for centuries. In addition to a plethora of health benefits, millets are also good for the environment with low water & input requirement. With the aim to create awareness and increase production & consumption of millets, United Nations, at the behest of the Government of India, declared 2023 the International Year Millets. 

Yoga and Health:

Yoga is an ancient physical, mental, and spiritual practice that originated in India. The word â€˜yogaâ€™ derives from Sanskrit and means to join or to unite, symbolizing the union of body and consciousness. Today it is practiced in various forms around the world and continues to grow in popularity.

Green Bharat:

By Planting a tree by each person, we can save the earth and play against of pollution, Plants are the only solution to clean the environment. 

Oil and Gas Conservation:

Conservation of petroleum products in the country. Increasing use of cleaner and eco-friendly gaseous fuels in the country. Conservation messages amongst the major consuming sectors transport, industry, agricultural, household, and commercial.

 

Students may also submit design samples for painting on any other relevant themes.

All Paintings should be original and have not been published elsewhere.

We're pleased to open applications for the *Finlatics Data Science Experience Program*, an *online live project* that helps you learn & gain work experience in *data science with Python* at the *National Institute of Technology, Raipur*.

*Benefits* post completion: 
*  *Certificate of Work Experience*
*  *Letter of Recommendation*
*  *Certificate of Proficiency in Python*

To apply, students can fill out the form below and we'll get in touch with them:

 https://www.finlatics.com/bads_application?utm_src=nitrai2w

As *Python would be taught* in the program, *no prerequisites* or prior domain knowledge are required to be a part of the program. *Live Sessions* would also be conducted to help *practice coding with Python*.

*Program Duration* : 2 months

*Program Start*: *Flexible* on student choice. Can be started *post-exams*. 

This project is running at *leading campuses* including *IIT Bombay, IIT Delhi, IIT Madras, and BITS Pilani* among others.
 
*Time Commitment*: 3 - 4 hours per week

If selected, the program has a minimal induction fee of Rs. 1999 + GST / 2999 + GST (on student choice)

*Fee Waiver*:  A *15 - 25%* *Fee Waiver* shall be given to all *NIT Raipur* students on the abovementioned minimal induction fee. This waiver will *reduce the fee* to Rs. 1690 + GST / Rs. 2199 + GST. 

To be eligible for the fee waiver, kindly apply through the abovementioned link only.

Looking forward to a fruitful engagement. 

Best regards,
Team Finlatics

20/02/2024, 16:22 - Aryan Kumar Chemical'26: The moisture content in vegetable oil is a critical factor affecting its quality and shelf life. Excessive moisture can accelerate oxidation, leading to rancidity and off-flavors, while also providing a favorable environment for microbial growth, potentially compromising safety. Moisture content is typically measured using Karl Fischer titration, a precise method for detecting trace amounts of water. Proper storage in cool, dry conditions and monitoring moisture levels are essential to prevent quality degradation. Regulatory bodies often set standards for moisture content in vegetable oil to ensure consumer safety and product quality, making it a key consideration in food processing and quality control.
